  "prompt": "How do I change gender in booked IRCTC e-tickets?",
  "response": "To change the gender in booked IRCTC e-tickets, you will typically need to follow these steps. However, it's important to note that the ability to change passenger details after booking is limited, and in cases like gender, you might need to cancel the ticket and book a new one. Here\u2019s a general guide:\n\n1. **Log in to your IRCTC Account**: Go to the IRCTC website or open the IRCTC app and log into your account.\n\n2. **View Booked Tickets**: Navigate to the 'My Bookings' section where you can view all your booked tickets.\n\n3. **Select the Ticket**: Choose the ticket for which you want to change the gender details.\n\n4. **Check Modification Options**: Look for a 'Modify' or 'Change Details' option, but be aware that IRCTC usually allows limited modifications post-booking. \n\n5. **Cancel and Rebook (if required)**: If you are unable to change the gender directly, you may need to cancel the ticket and book a new one with the correct details. Be aware of the cancellation policies and any fees that may apply when canceling.\n\n6. **Contact Customer Support**: If you have any difficulties or specific concerns, you can reach out to IRCTC customer support for assistance. They may be able to provide additional options or guidance based on your situation.\n\nKeep in mind that passenger details on an e-ticket, such as gender, are usually required to be accurate at the time of booking and changes may not always be accommodated once confirmed. Always double-check the details before finalizing the booking.",
